    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1313">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/75.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hostetter</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Hermosillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 13. Am informed by General Obregon whose brother-in-law is
                    manager of Almada Sugar refineries that plant belongs to Almada, was sold on
                    option to American company who did not comply with conditions and was returned
                    to Almada about two months before Obregón took Culiacán. Have wired Governor
                    Eiveros for full information and will wire answer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hostetter</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
